solutions.content:
I treated the question as a two-agent game in which each agent tries to maximize their utility. My code unfortunately leads to a TLE which I thought would be fixed if I implemented alpha-beta pruning, but it turns out the solution was much much simpler lol. Just thought I'd post what I did to add some variety to the solutions posted.

```
class Solution:
    def canWinNim(self, n: int) -> bool:
        def playNim(n, turn):
            if n < 0:
                return -2 # Impossible case, so we make utility -2
            if n == 0 and turn == 'M':
                return -1
            elif n == 0 and turn == 'O':
                return 1
            else:
                if turn == 'M':
                    return max(playNim(n-1, 'O'), playNim(n-2, 'O'), playNim(n-3, 'O'))
                else:
                    return min(playNim(n-1, 'M'), playNim(n-2, 'M'), playNim(n-3, 'M'))

        return playNim(n, 'M') == 1
```

