solutions.content:
**Math Solution:**

Players can take 1,2,3 stones in each turn and the player who removes last stone wins the game. As both
plays optimally they always try to take stones such a way that there are only 4 stones left. If there is only
4 stone left then the opponenet player can take at most 3 stones which leaves the player with 1 stone 
and the player wins. So if the total number of stone mod 4 = 0 then opponenet always make moves such
that at the end player left with only 4 stone and the opponent wins no matter what. So I can only win if
n mod 4 !=0.

