However, it's worth explaining how to come up with it. I came up with this idea by first thinking of DP. Since I take the first turn, and I can pick only 1, 2 or 3 stones, the recursive formula for DP is:

dp[ n ] = !dp[ n-1 ] || !dp[ n-2 ] || !dp[ n-3 ]

where dp[ n ] is a boolean variable, indicating whether I can win or not. If within 3 stones, there exists a way for me to lose the game, then there exists a way for me to win the game for the current number of stones , because I take the first turn.

