solutions.content:
***Brief note about Question-***
* We are given two strings and we have to find whether one string is subsequence of anthor is not.
* A subsequence of a string is a new string that is formed from the original string by deleting some (can be none) of the characters without disturbing the relative positions of the remaining characters. (i.e., "ace" is a subsequence of "abcde" while "aec" is not).
```
Let's take an example not given in question -
Suppose they are given strings like s = "abcd" and t = "aghsnbjijyoucyehd"

So, the answer should be true
because we are able to find string s in our string t

see, t = "aghsnbjijyoucyehd"
          ↑    ↑      ↑   ↑ 
		  a    b      c   d  
```
________________
***Solution - I (Using First Thought, Accepted)-***
* The first and very basic thing we will say that we move from in our `string t` and whenever we matches a character of the same as string s, we will `increase our j pointer` which covers all the character of string s.
* And lastly if we our` j pointer becomes equal to the length of s pointer`, we definately say we find string s in our string t.
* See code for below, it is too easy u got that just by seeing it.
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool isSubsequence(string s, string t) {
        int n1 = s.length(); // extracting length of string s
        int n2 = t.length(); // extracting length of string t

        // if length of string s is greater than string t, then it is impossible to find out s in t
        // say s = "abcdef" and t = "ab"
        if(n1 > n2)
        {
            return false;
        }

        // if both strings are empty, then definately return true
        if(n1 == 0 && n2 == 0)
        {
            return true;
        }

        int j = 0; // declaring j pointer which moves in string s

        // find variable which tells us whether we ae able to find string s in string t
        bool find = false; 

        // traverse from string t
        for(int i = 0; i < n2; i++)
        {
            // if character matches
            if(t[i] == s[j])
            {
                j++; // increase j pointer
            }

            // if at any point j pointer becomes equal the length of string s,
			//then we will say yes!! we find a string therefore,
			//put find as true and from now we don't need to travel, so break
            if(j == n1)
            {
                find = true;
                break;
            }
        }

        // and lastly if we are not able to find string s in string t,
        // then my find variable remains false, so 

        return find;  // so simply return find
    }
};
```
________
***Solution - II(Using Recursion , Accepted)-***
* We are also able to find the soloution using recursion.
* First, again put eye on statement, we have to find whether string s is subsequence of string t or not.
* So, we may start from either sides of the strings and start matching character.
* Here we start from last and match character.
* **How we will know whether we are able to apply recursion here or not?**
* For recursion, we will always have some choices, so question arieses whether choices are present here or not.
* We will say yess, we have choices, what choices? 
* We will say for every character of string t we have two choices, first, whether it matches with the character of string s and second whether it does not matches with the character of string s.
* So, We will do this only, for every character of string t and string s, we simply checks whether they both matches or not.
* **Anthor question arises, if recursion is their then when we stop?**
* Suppose at any point our came to know that no more character of string s is left to be matched then at that point we will say, since no character of string s is left to check, that means all characters of string s are now matched so we will return true.
* Again, suppose any point camw when string t is exhausted that means we don't have more characters left in string t, so we will return false.
* That's all, see code for better understanding.
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool solve(string &s, string &t, int n1, int n2)
    {
        if(n1 == 0) // if string s have no characters to left for comparing
        {
            return true; // then we easily say, all characters are now matched, so return true
        }

        if(n2 == 0) //  if string t have no characters to left for comparing
        {
            return false; // then we will say, it is not possible to find whether s is a subsequence of string t, so we will return false
        }

        // if last both characters are matched then,
        // decrease charcters in both the strigs
        if(s[n1 - 1] == t[n2 - 1])
        {
            return solve(s, t, n1 - 1, n2 - 1);
        }

        // if last both characters are not matched, 
        //then only decreae string t character
        return solve(s, t, n1, n2 - 1);

    }
    bool isSubsequence(string s, string t) {
        int n1 = s.length(); // extracting length of string s
        int n2 = t.length(); // extracting length of string t

        // return solve that tells us answer
       return solve(s, t, n1, n2);
    }
};
```
____________
***Solution - III(Using DP, memoziation , Accepted)-***
* We can further optimize our recursion by memoziation.
* We find the longest common subsequence (LCS) of string s and string t.
* **If the length of both LCS and string s is equal, we will say that yess!!, string s is a subsequence of string t**.
```
class Solution {
public:
    int t[1001][10001];

    int solve(string& first, string& sec, int n1, int n2)
    {
        // if length of any one of the string becomes zero, simply return 0
        if(n1 == 0 || n2 == 0)
        {
            return 0;
        }

        // if we already store this result
        if(t[n1][n2] != -1) 
            return t[n1][n2];

        // if last character matches of both strings, then add 1 to length
        if(first[n1 - 1] == sec[n2 - 1])
        {
            return t[n1][n2]  = 1 + solve(first, sec, n1 - 1, n2 - 1);
        }

        // if result is not alredy store, then we need to calculate
        if(t[n1 - 1][n2] == -1)
        {
            t[n1 - 1][n2] = solve(first, sec, n1 - 1, n2);
        }

        // if result is not alredy store, then we need to calculate
        if(t[n1][n2 - 1] == -1)
        {
            t[n1][n2 - 1] = solve(first, sec, n1, n2 - 1);
        }

        //return max of them
        return max(t[n1 - 1][n2], t[n1][n2 - 1]);
    }

    bool isSubsequence(string first, string second) {
        int n1 = first.length(); // extracting length of string s
        int n2 = second.length(); // extracting length of string t

        if(n1 > n2)
            return false;

        if(n1 == 0 && n2 == 0)
            return true;

        memset(t, -1, sizeof(t));

        int LCS = solve(first, second, n1, n2);

        // if LCS is equal to length of string s, then return true
        if(LCS == n1)
            return true;

        return false;
    }
};
```
