### **Intuition:**
1. We treat subsequence string as stack and travel from end of base string.
1. When the top() of stack matches current element in base string we pop().
1. We continue till we reach end of base string or till stick becomes empty. <br><br>

**Time complexity O(n)**
As we iterate only once in base string and till the end in worst case 

**Space Complexity O(1)**
As the only extra space required is of iteration variable

### **Dry Run:**
Consider **base string t: "bdaecf"** 

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/fdeef7f3-7dd1-4a83-8809-17cca30c2dc7_1646194851.7933378.png)

<br>

### CODE:
```
class Solution {
    public:
        bool isSubsequence(string s, string t) 
        {        
            for(int x=t.size()-1; x>=0 && !s.empty(); x--)
                if (t[x]==s[s.size()-1]) s.pop_back();   //treating subsequence string as a stack
            return s.empty();
        }
};
```

