# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Take a pointer to compare each character of string s with each character of string t.
2. Compare character of s with character of t, if they match then increment the pointer otherwise cotinue the process.
3. At the end if the pointer becomes equal or greater than length of s ,then it means that the string s is successfully checked and it is a subsequence of t hence return true.  

