Some of the most popular python solutions are a bit convoluted, so this is an attempt to write one that is easy to understand.

We use `index` to track our position in `s`. Whenever we encounter a letter in `t` which is the same as our current letter in `s` we increment `index`. If `index` reaches the length of `s` we know all of `s`'s characters were present in `t` in order.

```
def isSubsequence(self, s: str, t: str) -> bool:
    n = len(s)
    index = 0;
    for c in t:
        if index == n:
            break
        if c == s[index]:
            index += 1
    return n == index
```

