The logic of the code is as follows:

1 - The method iterates over each character "x" in the string "s".

2 - For each character "x", it checks if it is present in the string "t" using the "in" operator.

3 - If the character "x" is found in "t", it updates the string "t" by excluding the already tested character "x". This is done by finding the 
     position of the first occurrence of "x" using the "index" method, and then taking a slice of the string "t" starting from that position plus 
     one (t[t.index(x)+1:]). This effectively removes the character "x" from the remaining portion of "t".

4 - If the character "x" is not present in "t", it means that "s" cannot be a subsequence of "t". In this case, the method returns False.

5 - If all iterations are successfully completed, i.e., all characters of "s" have been found in "t" in the correct order while excluding the tested 
     characters, the method returns True.

